# Node Platform Standards

Validate inputs, avoid blocking CPU on request threads, enforce request timeouts, and prefer streaming for large payloads.

**Justification:** Prevents reliability and performance pitfalls in services and webhooks.

## Input Validation

```typescript
const validate = ajv.compile(schema);
if (!validate(body)) throw new Error('invalid');
```

## Concurrency & Timeouts

- Reject long CPU work on request threads; offload to workers/queues
- Enforce per-request timeouts and sensible connection pooling

